The presidential candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Bola Tinubu, has been declared the winner of the presidential election in Ogun state. The total number of registered voters in the state was 2,688,305 and the number of accredited to vote was 61234. According to the results announced on Monday by the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) collation officers for the 20 Local Government Areas (LGAs) in the state, Tinubu polled 341,554 votes. The Peoples Democratic Party presidential candidate, Atiku Abubakar, polled 123,831 votes,to emerge second. Peter Obi of the Labour Party trailed with 85,829 votes, and the New Nigeria Peoples Party (NNPP) presidential candidate, Rabiu Kwankwaso, polled 2,200 votes. 